        "_account_id": 1144,
        "name": "Praveen",
        "email": "praveen.solanki@gmail.com",
        "username": "solanki"
      },
      "date": "2025-06-07 16:59:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Adding man pages for llapi_lmv_get_uuids and llapi_lov_get_uuids\n\nLLAPI_LMV_GET_UUIDS(3)                    Lustre Library Functions                    LLAPI_LMV_GET_UUIDS(3)\n\nNAME\n       llapi_lmv_get_uuids, llapi_lov_get_uuids - Get device uuids\n\nSYNOPSIS\n       #include <lustre/lustreapi.h>\n\n       int llapi_lmv_get_uuids(int fd, struct obd_uuid *uuidp, int *mdt_count);\n       int llapi_lov_get_uuids(int fd, struct obd_uuid *uuidp, int *ost_count);\n\nDESCRIPTION\n       The functions llapi_lmv_get_uuids() llapi_lov_get_uuids(), gets the uuids for respective device type.\n\n       fd file decriptor for mount point, uuidp is preallocated array of obd_uuid to hold uuids\n\n       Count of devices.\n\nRETURN VALUES\n       Return the device uuids on success or a negative errno value on failure.\n\nAVAILABILITY\n       llapi_lmv_get_uuids()  llapi_lov_get_uuids()  is part of the lustre(7) user application interface li‐\n       brary since before release 2.17.0\n\nSEE ALSO\n       llapi_file_fget_lov_uuid(3),         llapi_file_get_lmv_uuid(3),          llapi_file_get_lov_uuid(3),\n       llapi_get_obd_count(3), llapi_search_ost(3), lustreapi(7)\n\nLustre User API                                  2025-06-05                           LLAPI_LMV_GET_UUIDS(3)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
